<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>GitHub Trending: FreeMarker, Today</title><link>https://github.com/trending/freemarker?since=daily</link><description>The top repositories on GitHub for freemarker, measured daily</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 Nov 2019 01:05:16 GMT</pubDate><lastBuildDate>Wed, 27 Nov 2019 01:05:16 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>PyRSS2Gen-1.1.0</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><ttl>720</ttl><item><title>mozilla/blurts-server #1 in FreeMarker, Today</title><link>https://github.com/mozilla/blurts-server</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Firefox Monitor arms you with tools to keep your personal information safe. Find out what hackers already know about you and learn how to stay a step ahead of them.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="readme" class="instapaper_body md" data-path="README.md"&gt;&lt;article class="markdown-body entry-content p-5" itemprop="text"&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-firefox-monitor-server" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#firefox-monitor-server"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Firefox Monitor Server&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-summary" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#summary"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Firefox Monitor notifies users when their credentials have been compromised in a data breach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This code is for the monitor.firefox.com service &amp;amp; website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Breach data is powered by &lt;a href="https://haveibeenpwned.com/" rel="nofollow"&gt;haveibeenpwned.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See the &lt;a href="https://haveibeenpwned.com/About" rel="nofollow"&gt;Have I Been Pwned about page&lt;/a&gt; for
the "what" and "why" of data breach alerts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-development" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#development"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Development&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-requirements" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#requirements"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://nodejs.org/" rel="nofollow"&gt;Node&lt;/a&gt; 8+ (with npm)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.postgresql.org/" rel="nofollow"&gt;Postgres&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-install" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#install"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Install&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clone and change to the directory:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;git clone https://github.com/mozilla/blurts-server.git
&lt;span class="pl-c1"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; blurts-server&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Install dependencies:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;npm install&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Copy the &lt;code&gt;.env-dist&lt;/code&gt; file to &lt;code&gt;.env&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;cp .env-dist .env&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-run" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#run"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Run&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the server:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;npm start&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: &lt;code&gt;npm start&lt;/code&gt; uses &lt;code&gt;onchange&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;nodemon&lt;/code&gt; to automatically detect file
changes, re-compile static assets, and restart the express process. If you want
more control, see the &lt;code&gt;scripts&lt;/code&gt; section of &lt;code&gt;package.json&lt;/code&gt; for more commands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start="2"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate to &lt;a href="http://localhost:6060/" rel="nofollow"&gt;localhost:6060/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-database" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#database"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Database&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To create the database tables ...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create the &lt;code&gt;blurts&lt;/code&gt; database:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;createdb blurts
createdb test-blurts &lt;span class="pl-c"&gt;&lt;span class="pl-c"&gt;#&lt;/span&gt; for tests&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update the &lt;code&gt;DATABASE_URL&lt;/code&gt; value in your &lt;code&gt;.env&lt;/code&gt; file with your local db
credentials:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;DATABASE_URL="postgres://&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;@localhost:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;/blurts"
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the migrations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;npm run db:migrate
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-emails" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#emails"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Emails&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The included &lt;code&gt;.env-dist&lt;/code&gt; sets &lt;code&gt;DEBUG_DUMMY_SMTP=1&lt;/code&gt; which disables emails.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To send emails, you'll need to unset &lt;code&gt;DEBUG_DUMMY_SMTP&lt;/code&gt; and supply real SMTP
config values for sending email.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can set and source these via the &lt;code&gt;.env&lt;/code&gt; file, or set them directly:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; DEBUG_DUMMY_SMTP=
&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; SMTP_HOST=&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;your-smtp-host&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; SMTP_PORT=&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;your-smtp-port&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; SMTP_USERNAME=&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;your-username&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; SMTP_PASSWORD=&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;your-password&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-firefox-accounts" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#firefox-accounts"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Firefox Accounts&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Subscribe with a Firefox Account is controlled via the &lt;code&gt;FXA_ENABLED&lt;/code&gt;
environment variable. (See &lt;code&gt;.env-dist&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The repo comes with a development FxA oauth app pre-configured in &lt;code&gt;.env&lt;/code&gt;, which
should work fine running the app on &lt;a href="http://localhost:6060" rel="nofollow"&gt;http://localhost:6060&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To use a different Firefox Accounts oauth relying party,
you'll need to &lt;a href="https://oauth-stable.dev.lcip.org/console/clients" rel="nofollow"&gt;create an FxA Oauth Client&lt;/a&gt; and then set some &lt;code&gt;OAUTH&lt;/code&gt; config values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can set and source these via the &lt;code&gt;.env&lt;/code&gt; file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;your-fxa-oauth-client-id&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;your-fxa-oauth-client-secret&lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
OAUTH_AUTHORIZATION_URI=&lt;span class="pl-s"&gt;&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;"&lt;/span&gt;https://oauth-stable.dev.lcip.org/v1/authorization&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
OAUTH_PROFILE_URI=&lt;span class="pl-s"&gt;&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;"&lt;/span&gt;https://stable.dev.lcip.org/profile/v1/profile&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
OAUTH_TOKEN_URI=&lt;span class="pl-s"&gt;&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;"&lt;/span&gt;https://oauth-stable.dev.lcip.org/v1/token&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-testing" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#testing"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Testing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The full test suite can be run via &lt;code&gt;npm test&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-individual-tests" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#individual-tests"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Individual tests&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To run individual tests, use &lt;code&gt;NODE_ENV=tests&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;jest&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;NODE_ENV=tests jest --runInBand tests/home.test.js
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To run tests with interactive &lt;code&gt;debugger&lt;/code&gt; lines enabled:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;NODE_ENV=tests node inspect --harmony ./node_modules/.bin/jest tests/home.test.js
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-lint" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#lint"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Lint&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After installing the dependencies, you can lint the code by calling:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;npm run lint&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-deployment" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#deployment"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Deployment&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Firefox Monitor Breach Alerts is designed with &lt;a href="https://12factor.net/" rel="nofollow"&gt;12-factor&lt;/a&gt; methodology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-deploy-on-heroku" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#deploy-on-heroku"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Deploy on Heroku&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to set some required environment variables on Heroku.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-shell"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;heroku config:set COOKIE_SECRET=unsafe-cookie-secret-for-heroku
heroku config:set DEBUG_DUMMY_SMTP=1&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And any others, depending on the features you're running on Heroku - e.g.,
Email or Firefox Accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
